  "text": "The xDS DiscoveryResponse processing chain in Envoy flows as follows:\n\n**1. gRPC Stream Handler (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h)**\nThe GrpcStream template class receives DiscoveryResponse messages from the gRPC stream via its onReceiveMessage() method (line 85-95). When a response is received, it immediately calls the callbacks_->onDiscoveryResponse() callback with the response message and control plane stats.\n\n**2. Discovery Response Handling (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.cc)**\nThe GrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse() method (line 313) is the main handler. It:\n- Validates that the type_url matches an active subscription\n- Handles control plane identifiers from the response\n- Decodes resources and validates them\n- Calls processDiscoveryResources() to dispatch updates\n- Handles exceptions and sends NACKs if validation fails\n- Updates the response_nonce for ACK tracking\n\n**3. Resource Processing & Validation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.cc, line 413-515)**\nThe GrpcMuxImpl::processDiscoveryResources() method:\n- Executes external config validators if configured\n- Iterates through watches (subscriptions) for the type_url\n- Maps requested resource names to the received resources\n- Calls watch->callbacks_.onConfigUpdate() for each watch with the matched resources\n- Updates the resource cache for EDS resources if applicable\n- Calls the xDS resources delegate if configured\n- Updates the request's version_info field\n\n**4. Resource Version Bookkeeping**\nTwo implementations track resource versions:\n- **SotwSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h)**: Tracks state-of-the-world subscriptions with a single version_info per type_url\n- **DeltaSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h)**: Tracks delta subscriptions with per-resource versions using the ResourceState class (line 51-73 in .h). The ResourceState class has methods like isWaitingForServer(), setVersion(), and version() to manage individual resource version tracking. Initial resource versions are sent in DiscoveryRequests (line 251, 258 in .cc) for reconnection scenarios.\n\n**5. Listener Update Dispatch (source/common/listener_manager/lds_api.cc, line 48-100)**\nLdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate() handles listener configuration updates:\n- Pauses RDS/SDS subscriptions during listener update to avoid conflicts\n- Calls listener_manager_.beginListenerUpdate()\n- Removes listeners first by calling listener_manager_.removeListener() for each removed_resource\n- Adds/updates listeners by calling listener_manager_.addOrUpdateListener() with the listener config and resource version\n- Handles errors and records failure states\n- Calls listener_manager_.endListenerUpdate() with failure states\n\n**6. Cluster Update Dispatch (source/common/upstream/cds_api_impl.cc, line 40-75)**\nCdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate() handles cluster configuration updates:\n- Computes which existing clusters need to be removed (those not in the response)\n- Calls helper_.onConfigUpdate() with added_resources and removed_resources\n- Runs any initialization callbacks\n- Returns status indicating success or errors\n\n**Supporting Infrastructure**\n- SubscriptionCallbacks (envoy/config/subscription.h): Base interface for configuration update callbacks\n- GrpcMuxContext (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_context.h): Contains context needed for gRPC stream creation, including async_client_, service_method_, dispatcher_, and configuration validators\n- The unified xDS mux implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc) creates GrpcStream objects and manages subscription state factories for both SotW and Delta variants\n\nThe complete flow: gRPC response → GrpcStream::onReceiveMessage → GrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse → processDiscoveryResources → watch callbacks (LdsApiImpl/CdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate) → listener_manager/cluster_manager updates."
}

